Zimbabwe’s NetOne Borrows $60 Million, Newsday Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-08-24T06:46:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/zimbabwe-s-netone-borrows-60-million-newsday-reports.html
NetOne Cellular,  Zimbabwe ’s state-
owned mobile phone operator, has borrowed $60 million so it can
develop a broadband network,  Newsday  said, citing Managing
Director, Reward Kangai.  The loan was provided by China Export-Import Bank, the
Infrastructure Development Bank of Zimbabwe, CBZ Bank Ltd. and
BancABC Ltd., Harare-based Newsday said. NetOne plans to be able
to offer broadband services by the end of the year, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
